prefecthq/prefect#18664.body:
### Describe the current behavior

It would be nice to have the standard app.kubernete.io labels added to the k8s jobs started by the prefect-kubernetes worker. This would also enable automatic integration in observability tools where these fields are scraped by default.

I am open to contribute to this.


### Describe the proposed behavior

Labels are added. See example

### Example Use

I am currently running my custom worker like this:

```python
from prefect_kubernetes.worker import KubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration as PrefectKubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration

class KubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration(PrefectKubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration):

    @staticmethod
    def _base_work_pool_labels(work_pool: "WorkPool | None") -> dict[str, str]:
        labels = PrefectKubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration._base_work_pool_labels(work_pool)
        if work_pool is not None:
            labels["app.kubernetes.io/managed-by"] = str(work_pool.id) # could also be the worker name
        return labels

    @staticmethod
    def _base_deployment_labels(deployment: "DeploymentResponse | None") -> dict[str, str]:
        labels = PrefectKubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration._base_deployment_labels(deployment)
        if deployment is not None:
            labels["app.kubernetes.io/part-of"] = "prefect"
            labels["app.kubernetes.io/name"] = str(deployment.name)
        return labels

    @staticmethod
    def _base_flow_labels(flow: Flow | None) -> dict[str, str]:
        labels = PrefectKubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration._base_flow_labels(flow)
        if flow is not None:
            labels["app.kubernetes.io/component"] = flow.name
        return labels

    @staticmethod
    def _base_flow_run_labels(flow_run: FlowRun) -> dict[str, str]:
        labels = PrefectKubernetesWorkerJobConfiguration._base_flow_run_labels(flow_run)
        labels["app.kubernetes.io/instance"] = str(flow_run.name)
        labels["app.kubernetes.io/version"] = prefect.__version__
        return labels
```

